1 (6) Any resident serviceman on furlough of more than three (3) days in this state may,
2 without any Kentucky sport hunting or sport fishing licenses, do any act authorized
3 by the licenses, but while so doing he or she shall carry on his or her person proper
4 identification and papers showing his or her furlough status.
5 (7) (a) Landowners, their spouses or dependent children, or their designee who must
6 be approved by the department[commissioner], who kill or trap on their lands
7 any wildlife causing damage to the lands or any personal property situated
8 thereon shall not be required to have a hunting or trapping license and may do
9 so during periods other than the open season for the particular species with a
10 deer destruction permit[without a tag] and dispose of the carcass on-site.
11 Tenants, their spouses, their dependent children, or other persons approved by
12 the department[commissioner], shall also have the same privilege.
13 (b) Individuals specified in paragraph (a) of this subsection whose lands or
14 personal property has been damaged by wildlife may request a deer
15 destruction permit from the department. Within fifteen (15) days of
16 receiving the request, the department shall inspect and confirm any damage
17 to the lands or personal property caused by wildlife. Upon confirmation of
18 damage, the department shall issue to the requesting individual a minimum
19 of five (5) deer destruction permits each year for the duration of a two (2)
20 year period. The deer destruction permit shall authorize the individual to
21 take antlerless deer outside of an established hunting season for a period of
22 two (2) years from the date of confirmation of damage to the lands or
23 personal property.
24 (c) The department shall grant immediate renewal of a deer destruction permit
25 if the permitted individuals provide verification of continued damage to the
26 lands or personal property by submitting a:
27 1. Time-and date-stamped electronic image; or
Page 2 of 6
XXXX 1/6/2026 8:49 AM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 864
1 2. Current crop production report.
2 (d) Any landowner or individual specified in paragraph (a) of this subsection
3 who has been issued a deer destruction permit by the department during the
4 three (3) year period prior to the effective date of this Act may request
5 renewal of an existing deer destruction permit by providing verification of
6 continued damage to the lands or personal property by submitting to the
7 department a:
8 1. Time-and date-stamped electronic image: or
9 2. Current crop production report.
10 (e) Upon destruction of any wildlife by[ the above-specified] individuals
11 specified in paragraph (a) of this subsection, the act shall be reported to a
12 game warden within twenty-four (24) hours of the kill. Individuals wishing to
13 transport the carcass from the property upon which it was killed shall contact
14 personnel of the department to request a disposal tag or other authorization.
15 Inedible parts from wildlife taken under the authorization of this section shall
16 not be utilized for any purpose and shall be destroyed or left on the property
17 on which the taking occurred[afield].
18 (f) The department shall issue a deer permit allowing the taking of one (1)
19 additional antlered deer per hunting season to any landowner or individual
20 specified in paragraph (a) of this subsection who:
21 1. Has taken and reported to the department a minimum of three (3)
22 antlerless deer during the current hunting season in accordance with
23 the provisions of this chapter and the administrative regulations
24 promulgated by the department; and
25 2. Requests to the department that an additional deer permit be issued.
26 (g) The department shall promulgate administrative regulations establishing
27 procedures for the designee appointment process, including request and
