1 approval deadlines.
2 (8) If a reciprocal agreement is entered into by the commissioner, with the approval of
3 the commission, and promulgated as an administrative regulation by the department
4 and similar action is taken by the appropriate authority in Missouri, Tennessee,
5 Virginia, West Virginia, Indiana, Ohio, or Illinois, persons holding a resident or
6 nonresident fishing or a resident or nonresident hunting license issued in these
7 states shall be permitted to perform the acts authorized by the license upon certain
8 contiguous waters and land areas adjacent to the common boundaries of the above-
9 mentioned states and the State of Kentucky. A resident of the State of Kentucky
10 shall purchase a proper Kentucky license to conform with the reciprocal agreement.
11 (9) Any member of the Kentucky Army or Air National Guard, active duty or Reserve
12 Component, in any branch in the United States Armed Forces that is based in the
13 Commonwealth of Kentucky, shall have the right to take fish or hunt on any
14 military property belonging to the Commonwealth without procuring any sport
15 hunting or sport fishing license.
16 (10) A person not otherwise exempted from hunter safety education or from procuring
17 any sport hunting or sport fishing license shall be exempt from the department-
18 sanctioned live-fire exercise component of the hunter education course requirement
19 if he or she:
20 (a) Is a current member of the Armed Forces of the United States;
21 (b) Has served in the Armed Forces of the United States and was discharged or
22 released therefrom under conditions other than dishonorable; or
23 (c) Is a peace officer certified pursuant to KRS 15.380 to 15.404.
24 Section 2. KRS 150.390 is amended to read as follows:
25 (1) No person shall possess, take, pursue, or attempt to take or pursue or otherwise
26 molest any wild elk, deer, wild turkey, or bear in any manner contrary to any
27 provisions of this chapter or its regulations.
Page 4 of 6
XXXX 1/6/2026 8:49 AM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 864
1 (2) No person shall use a dog to chase or molest wild elk or deer in any manner, at any
2 time, or at any place. Any game warden, peace officer, sheriff, or constable may
3 take necessary steps to stop, prevent, or bring under control any dog or dogs found
4 chasing or molesting wild elk or deer at any time.
5 (3) The department shall establish by administrative regulation the conditions under
6 which depredation permits may be issued without cost to persons suffering damage
7 from wild elk to allow the taking of wild elk.
8 (4) If Kentucky's wild elk population reaches a level that will sustain limited hunting,
9 the department may establish by administrative regulations the conditions and
10 permits that would allow the controlled taking of wild elk.
11 (5) The department shall identify areas where deer and elk pose a significant threat to
12 agriculture or to health and human safety from automobile accidents and may take
13 necessary steps to reduce the deer and elk population in those areas. Methods to
14 reduce the deer and elk population may include but are not limited to the following:
15 (a) Special hunts;
16 (b) Increasing the doe harvest; and
17 (c) Working with the Transportation Cabinet to make vegetation along highways
18 unpalatable to deer and elk.
19 (6) Immediately following the conclusion of a muzzle-loading gun season in
20 December and for a period of ten (10) consecutive days, any person that is in
21 compliance with licensing or permitting requirements:
22 (a) May take antlerless deer using:
23 1. Archery equipment;
24 2. A muzzle-loading gun; or
25 3. A modern gun including;
26 a. An air gun;
27 b. A handgun;
Page 5 of 6
XXXX 1/6/2026 8:49 AM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 864
1 c. A rifle; or
2 d. A shotgun; and
3 (b) Shall abide by any other wildlife hunting season dates and limits as set forth
4 by the department for the management and conservation of wildlife.
5 Section 3. Whereas in an effort to curb increased destruction of vital
6 agricultural crops throughout the Commonwealth, an emergency is declared to exist, and
7 this Act takes effect upon its passage and approval by the Governor or upon its otherwise
8 becoming a law.
